point : sexist advertising harm woman through objectification and diminishing of self image . the united nations convention to eliminate discrimination against women cedaw link stereotype about woman to prejudice base on gender . 1 through visual and verbal message woman be portray a subservient to men . women be see increasingly a sex object and these ad legitimize violence against woman . 2 sexist advertising also harm women's self image by portray an ideal stylize body . 3 the implied message be that consumer should seek to acquire these image even if they be contrary to the reality of body type and feature . eating disorder and obsessive beauty product consumption result in order to attain ideal beauty image present in the medium . 4 sexist ad also harm men through stereotyped image of masculinity . 51 object . org . women not sex objects . 2011 august 24 1 2 newswise . com . study find rise in sexualized images of women . 2011 08 10 2 3 kilbourne , jean . beauty . . . and the beast of advertising 3 
counterpoint : sexist advertising reflect current social attitude . attitudes and perception be base on culturally specific value and belief . it be difficult to determine a universal definition of harm and sexist advertising to determine if harm occurs . some study have be question regard their rigor in examine the direct link from advertising to violence against woman . 1 violence to woman be not debatable but the cause of that violence be . in addition , study relate to body image and beauty be often restrict to those share certain genetic characteristic yet biological difference exist between woman . what be an idealized body image exactly ? some current advertising have broaden image of woman to include a variety of body type , culture , and age to define beauty outside traditional stereotype . advertising also portray woman in role of power and success and not always a sex object a claimed . 1 young , toby . the home office report on child sexualisation be a 100 page cosmopolitan article . telegraph . com . 2010 february 26 4 
point : women's right to be free from stereotype , prejudice , discrimination and objectification should be a matter of deep concern a they infringe on human right relate to gender . advertising message influence young generation as well a send stereotypical image of men . as a result the objectification and violence against woman will continue . gender inequality and sexual harassment in the work place be not likely to diminish . 1 this mean that woman will continue to suffer from discrimination base upon their gender . 1 newswise . com , 2 study find rise in sexualized images of women . 2 2010 2 
counterpoint : bans on sexist advertising will not necessarily solve the harm present and could instead cause harm to business through restrict their ability to compete for audience and consumer . gender difference and belief about sex exist before advertising . there be no certainty change the content of ad would bring about change within individual society and culture which have their own independent attitude . cultures have a right to their own ideal and own value . 
point : adverts occupy more public space than ever before in history . due to technology , public space be global and ad can be see around the world , in 2009 the uk become the first major economy where advertiser spend more on internet advertising than on television advertising1 . through such dominance , ad contribute to attitude and value . due to their power to influence attitude within a society , serious attention should be pay to the content of advertising . 1 sweney , mark , 'internet overtake television to become big advertising sector in the uk' , the guardian , 30 september 2009 7 
counterpoint : all type of message be prevalent and advertisement do not possess any more influence than news or entertainment programming . advertising be simply integral to pubic space message and represent the increase of all message through the advancement of technology . advertising be also necessary to support all of type of other mediated message like news , politics , and entertainment . additionally , due to the overload of message of all kind , consumer learn to screen out and limit their reception of information . through technology , a viewer can eliminate advertisement from program content . 
point : norway and denmark have already develop policy to restrict sexist advertising1 . in 2008 , the un committee to eliminate discrimination against women call upon state to take action and in particular the united kingdom government to address this issue . 2 in may of 2011 parliamentary assembly of the council of europe 's committee on equal opportunity for women make a case for sexist advertising a a barrier to gender equality . in that report standard be present and method to cope with sexist advertising be suggest . 3 in australia a government advisory board have develop a list of principle to guide both advertising and the fashion industry . 41 holmes , stefanie . scandinavian split on sexist ad . bbc news . 2008 april 25 access 2011 08 25 9 2 object . com . women be not sex objects . 1 3 parliamentary assembly of 26 may 2011 , the council of europe . 10 4 kennedy , jean . fashion industry ask to adopt body image code . abcnews . 2010 june 27 11 
counterpoint : policies which ban will interfere with business practice , restrict free expression , and be be difficult to standardize . if ad do not sell , they will be reject and when ad be effective they be likely to continue in pursuit of gain consumer . business have the right to set business practice which work for them . restricting the content of advertising restricts free expression . in fact , sweden reject a ban on sexist advertising because it be believe to restrict free expression . 11 holmes , stefanie . scandinavian split on sexist ad bbcnews 9 
